Origin: DHI-internal (fix for upstream tool/sync_default_gems.rb erb recipe)
Description: Make sync_default_gems.rb's erb recipe copy the whole lib/erb/
 directory, not just lib/erb.rb. Upstream's recipe does
 `rm_rf(%w[lib/erb* test/erb libexec/erb])` (a FileUtils.rm_rf with the literal
 path "lib/erb*", which globs nothing and removes nothing) and then only
 `cp_r lib/erb.rb`. As a result lib/erb/version.rb is never refreshed from the
 synced gem, so after syncing e.g. erb v4.0.4.1 the ERB::VERSION constant (and
 thus the installed default gemspec) still reports the old version even though
 the fixed ERB#def_method code in lib/erb.rb was updated. CVE scanners key on
 the gemspec version, so the sync silently leaves the gem looking unpatched.
 This corrects rm_rf to real paths and copies lib/erb/ so version.rb (and the
 rest of the split sources) come from the synced gem. The context is identical
 in the Ruby 3.3 and 3.4 tool, so one patch applies to both.
Forwarded: no (would be a reasonable upstream fix; not yet submitted)

diff --git a/tool/sync_default_gems.rb b/tool/sync_default_gems.rb
--- a/tool/sync_default_gems.rb
+++ b/tool/sync_default_gems.rb
@@ -322,8 +322,9 @@ module SyncDefaultGems
       rm_rf("test/did_you_mean/lib")
       rm_rf(%w[test/did_you_mean/tree_spell/test_explore.rb])
     when "erb"
-      rm_rf(%w[lib/erb* test/erb libexec/erb])
+      rm_rf(%w[lib/erb.rb lib/erb test/erb libexec/erb])
       cp_r("#{upstream}/lib/erb.rb", "lib")
+      cp_r("#{upstream}/lib/erb", "lib")
       cp_r("#{upstream}/test/erb", "test")
       cp_r("#{upstream}/erb.gemspec", "lib")
       cp_r("#{upstream}/libexec/erb", "libexec")
